- Will track page navigation and performance metrics automatically

## Next Steps for User

To start collecting Speed Insights data:

1. **Deploy to Vercel**: Push the code to your Vercel-connected repository
2. **Enable in Dashboard**: Navigate to your project's Speed Insights tab in the Vercel dashboard
3. **Click Enable**: Activate Speed Insights for your deployment
4. **Wait for Data**: Metrics will appear after the site receives visitor traffic (may take a few days)

## Notes

- The implementation uses the React-specific import (`@vercel/speed-insights/react`) as recommended for React applications
- The component is already properly placed and requires no configuration props for basic usage
- Speed Insights will automatically track Core Web Vitals and other performance metrics
- The script will create routes at `/_vercel/speed-insights/*` after deployment to Vercel
- Lock files (`package-lock.json`) are already up-to-date with current dependencies

